It's fine. You
didn't. like. kill him.

427
00:30:46.803 --> 00:30:48.304
How was he killed?

428
00:30:49.597 --> 00:30:51.266
Oh. he wasn't.

429
00:30:51.349 --> 00:30:53.244
Are you fucking with me right now?

430
00:30:53.268 --> 00:30:56.062
Uh. no. it was. it was cancer.

431
00:30:57.564 --> 00:30:58.773
Shit.

432
00:31:00.733 --> 00:31:01.818
Yeah.

433
00:31:03.528 --> 00:31:06.573
- How old were you?
- I was 14.

434
00:31:06.656 --> 00:31:09.534
- So recently.
- Not really.

435
00:31:10.785 --> 00:31:12.620
I feel like
that's kind of recent.

436
00:31:13.663 --> 00:31:16.332
I don't know. I guess.

437
00:31:16.416 --> 00:31:18.835
Honestly it feels like
fuckin' forever ago.

438
00:31:20.837 --> 00:31:22.630
Is that why you
started doing drugs?

439
00:31:22.714 --> 00:31:25.675
That's
funny. That's what. uh...

440
00:31:25.758 --> 00:31:28.261
That's what everybody
asks in rehab.

441
00:31:28.344 --> 00:31:30.656
- What do you mean?
- Uh. just that. you know. like.

442
00:31:30.680 --> 00:31:33.099
I wish it was that
simple. you know. like...

443
00:31:33.182 --> 00:31:35.643
"Well. my dad died. so
I started doing drugs."

444
00:31:35.727 --> 00:31:37.061
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

445
00:31:37.145 --> 00:31:39.480
I feel like everyone's
looking for like a...

446
00:31:39.564 --> 00:31:41.482
cause and effect.

447
00:31:41.566 --> 00:31:43.985
Sometimes shit's
just like is what it is.

448
00:31:44.068 --> 00:31:45.778
Yeah. exactly.

449
00:31:45.862 --> 00:31:47.488
I don't know.

450
00:31:47.572 --> 00:31:49.449
To be honest. if my
dad was still here.

451
00:31:49.532 --> 00:31:51.409
I'd probably still
be doin' this shit.

452
00:31:55.872 --> 00:31:58.291
How does Jules not know
that you're doing drugs?

453
